tldr: The user requested to implement a database for questionnaire responses, an
  admin dashboard for data access, and an authentication system. The project
  successfully implemented a PostgreSQL database with Prisma, API routes for
  data management, and a simple password-based admin dashboard secured by
  Next.js middleware.
overview: The user initiated a project to enhance a sleep questionnaire
  application by adding database functionality, an admin dashboard, and an
  authentication system. The process began with an evaluation of the existing
  codebase against the provided SOW, identifying key missing components. A plan
  was then developed, focusing on using NeonDB (PostgreSQL) with Prisma for
  database management, creating API endpoints for questionnaire response
  handling (save, retrieve, CSV export), and building a simple admin dashboard.
  A crucial decision involved the authentication mechanism; initially, a custom
  session management system was implemented, but this was later streamlined to
  leverage Next.js middleware for more efficient and cleaner route protection
  using a basic cookie. The implementation involved updating demographic fields,
  defining the Prisma schema, creating API routes, and developing the login and
  dashboard pages. Comprehensive testing confirmed that all database operations,
  API endpoints, and the authentication system were fully functional, with the
  only minor hiccup being a client-side form submission issue during browser
  testing that did not affect the backend's integrity.
